      <text xml:space="preserve">[[File:Battery Park City 003.JPG|thumb|The esplanade of Battery Park City]]
[[File:Battery Park City 008.JPG|thumb|South End Avenue]]
'''Battery Park City''' is a 92-acre (0.4&amp;nbsp;km²) [[planned community]] at the southwestern tip of [[lower Manhattan]] in [[New York City]], [[United States]]. The land upon which it stands was created on the [[Hudson River]] using 1.2 million cubic yards (917,000 m&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;) of soil and rocks excavated during the construction of the [[World Trade Center]] and certain other construction projects, as well as from sand dredged from New York Harbor off Staten Island.&lt;ref&gt;Howe, Arthur. [http://infoweb.newsbank.com/iw-search/we/InfoWeb?p_action=doc&amp;p_docid=0EB293F7999CF967&amp;p_docnum=5&amp;p_queryname=NaN&amp;p_produ